{
  "Path": "Documentation/CoreDocumentation/AppManagement/Security",
  "Name": "Security",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:12.2835667+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<div class=\"documentation\"><h2>Accessing Core Security Management </h2><p class=\"mainText\">You this functionality through the App Management Tabs. From the Security tab you can manage\n        multiple things, including what roles exist in the system &amp; what particular tasks they can carry out within the\n        portal.</p><h2>The UI </h2><p class=\"mainText\">When you access the security tab, you&rsquo;re greeted with something that looks like this:</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/SecurityTab-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">This grid shows the bare minimum amount of roles that are required for our system and they\n        determine what can be viewed/interacted with in a particular scenario. For example if you&rsquo;re not logged in\n        (guest), the access you have is massively limited. If you&rsquo;re a new user (users) then you have access to more\n        than a guest would have, however this is still limited to what privileges you&rsquo;ve been granted as a user. And of\n        course, administrators have a lot more privileges than normal users do. </p><p class=\"mainText\">Expanding the users one gives you another grid that looks like this:</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/UsersTab-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">Within this expanded view, you can manage what users are in each role and remove them from the\n        roles if necessary. You will also see that there is a Privileges tab in this expanded view, this is a way to\n        control each of the roles and what actions they can carry out. As an example (see the following screenshot),\n        users are only able to &ldquo;read&rdquo; (view) apps and are unable to create, update and delete them as those are tasks\n        that can only be carried out by admins in this case. </p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/PrivilegesTab-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">Selecting which privileges should be applied to a role is done simply by just selecting the\n        appropriate boxes on the appropriate grid rows.</p><p class=\"mainText\">&nbsp;</p><h2>Adding a User to a Role </h2><p class=\"mainText\">There are two ways in which you can add a user to a role, the first way is to click the\n        <strong>&ldquo;Add User By Id&rdquo; </strong>button which will bring up a dialog that looks something like this:\n    </p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/AddUserByIdDialog-en.png\" width=\"765\" height=\"227\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">In here, you must enter the user&rsquo;s Id into the text box and press confirm. If the user&rsquo;s Id is\n        unknown to you, then you can click on the <strong>&ldquo;Add Users&rdquo;</strong> button that will bring up a dialog that\n        looks something\n        like this:</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/AddUsersDialog-en.png\" width=\"771\" height=\"577\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">Here you must find the user you wish to add to the role. If you click the filter buttons at the\n        top of the columns, you can search for a specific user which will make it easier to add them to the role you\n        wish to. For example, to add User 12345 to the User&rsquo;s role here you would select the top row and then click the\n        confirm button. This will then grant the user the privileges associated with that role.</p><p class=\"mainText\">&nbsp;</p><h2>Creating a Role </h2><p class=\"mainText\">To create a new role in this UI, you click on the <strong>&ldquo;New Role&rdquo;</strong> button in the\n        header bar. Clicking this will bring up a dialog that looks something like this:</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/CreateRoleDialog-en.png\" width=\"811\" height=\"197\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">Creating a Role is incredibly simple, only requiring you to add a name to it. Once you&rsquo;ve\n        filled in this field and clicked confirm, your new role will now exist in the system. You can then begin\n        applying specific privileges to it and add users to it.</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/TestRole-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">For now, I have created a test role to demonstrate how a new one would look within the existing\n        list.</p><p class=\"mainText\">&nbsp;</p><h2>Updating a Role </h2><p class=\"mainText\">You can edit the name you&rsquo;ve given to your role by just clicking on it within the grid:</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/UpdateRole-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /><p class=\"mainText\">Once you&rsquo;ve made any changes you want, you click the <strong>&ldquo;Save&rdquo;</strong> button on the\n        corresponding grid row and any changes you&rsquo;ve made will be saved.</p><p class=\"mainText\">&nbsp;</p><h2>Deleting a Role </h2><p class=\"mainText\">To delete a role that you no longer want or need then you click the <strong>&ldquo;Delete&rdquo;</strong> button that will\n        remove your role and from the our system.</p><img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/Core Documentation/App Management/Security/DeleteRole-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /></div>"
    }
  ],
  "PageInfo": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Description": "How to access and manage the roles and security in the portal.",
      "Title": "Security"
    }
  ]
}
"""
            },
            new PackageItem
            {
                Type = "Core/Page",
                Data = """
{
  "Path": "Documentation/SSODocumentation/ForgottenYourPassword",
  "Name": "Forgotten Your Password",
  "ResourceKey": "",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:13.0852673+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<div class=\"documentation\">\n\t<h2>Forgotten your Password? </h2>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">When you visit your portal in your browser, the first page you&rsquo;re greeted with is the login\n        page that looks something like this:</p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Forgot your Password/LoginPage-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" width=\"1113\" height=\"469\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">If you are having trouble signing into your account, you can click the <strong>&ldquo;Forgot\n Password&rdquo;</strong> button\n        that is underneath the <strong>&ldquo;User&rdquo;</strong> and <strong>&ldquo;Password&rdquo;</strong> fields. This will bring up a\n        dialog that looks something like this:\n    </p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Forgot your Password/PasswordResetDialog-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">In this dialog, you must enter the email address which you used to sign up with, this will then\n        send you an email with a link to change your password. The email will come through to your inbox and will look\n        something like this:\n    </p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Forgot your Password/PasswordResetEmail-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">When you click the link, it takes you to the page to reset your password that looks something\n        like this:</p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Forgot your Password/NewPasswordDialog-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">Here in the <strong>&ldquo;Password&rdquo;</strong> field you enter your new password and in the <strong>&ldquo;Confirm Password&rdquo;</strong> field\n        and press submit to save the changes to your password. This will now be the password you need to use to sign in.\n    </p>\n</div>"
    }
  ],
  "PageInfo": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Description": "This page explains the process of resetting your password if you happen to have forgotten it.",
      "Title": "Forgotten Your Password"
    }
  ]
}
"""
            },
            new PackageItem
            {
                Type = "Core/Page",
                Data = """
{
  "Path": "Documentation/SSODocumentation/ManagingyourProfile",
  "Name": "Managing your Profile",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:13.1084299+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<div class=\"documentation\">\n\t<h2>Managing your Profile </h2>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">When you are logged into the portal, you will see that in the top right there&rsquo;s something that\n        looks like this:</p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Managing Your Profile/HeaderDetails-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">At the top the culture selection which allows you to select the language you want to view the\n        portal in. Below that displays the current date and time. In order to view your profile you click on your\n        username, this will bring up a dialog that looks something like this: </p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Managing Your Profile/EditProfileDialog-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">Here, your <strong>&ldquo;Username&rdquo;</strong> cannot be edited as this is what you use to sign into\n        the portal, your\n        <strong>&ldquo;Display Name&rdquo;</strong> can be edited and this is what is displayed in the top right as your profile\n        name, <strong>&ldquo;Email&rdquo;</strong> is\n        where you want any emails from us to be sent to, typically this is your company email address. <strong>&ldquo;Phone\n Number&rdquo;</strong>\n should be populated with your company contact number, however this information is not required.\n        <strong>&ldquo;Culture&rdquo;</strong>\n defines what culture you&rsquo;d like the application to be displayed in be default, setting this to French (France)\n        for example will ensure that the portal is in French once you&rsquo;ve logged in. To save any changes you&rsquo;ve made to\n        your profile, you click the <strong>&ldquo;Confirm&rdquo;</strong> button.\n    </p>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">From this dialog, you can also change your password. When you click the <strong>&ldquo;Change\n Password&rdquo;</strong>\n button, a dialog that looks something like this comes up:</p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Managing Your Profile/ChangePasswordDialog-en.png\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">Here, you must enter your current password in the <strong>&ldquo;Old Password&rdquo;</strong> field and in the next two\n        fields you need to populate them with whatever you wish to set your new password to. Clicking <strong>&ldquo;Confirm&rdquo;</strong> will\n        save any changes you&rsquo;ve made</p>\n</div>"
    }
  ],
  "PageInfo": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Description": "this page explains how you can view and edit your portal profile.",
      "Title": "Managing your Profile"
    }
  ]
}
"""
            },
            new PackageItem
            {
                Type = "Core/Page",
                Data = """
{
  "Path": "Documentation/SSODocumentation/LoggingIn",
  "Name": "Logging In",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:13.1379108+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<div class=\"documentation\">\n\t<h2>Logging In to the Portal </h2>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">When you visit your portal in your browser, the first page you&rsquo;re greeted with is the login page\n        that looks something like this:</p>\n\t<img src=\"[app[root]]Api/DMS/Content/Documentation/SSO Documentation/Logging In/LoginPage-en.png\"/>\n\t<p class=\"mainText\">Here, you must enter your <strong>&ldquo;User Name&rdquo;</strong> and <strong>&ldquo;Password&rdquo;</strong> to the account you want to access and click\n        the <strong>&ldquo;Submit&rdquo;</strong> button to gain access.</p>\n</div>"
