}
"""
            },
            new PackageItem
            {
                Type = "Core/Page",
                Data = """
{
  "Path": "Documentation/SSODocumentation/Registration",
  "Name": "Registration",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:13.153507+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<h2>Registering to the Portal</h2><p>When you first access the portal you want to register, you'll be greeted with their login page. To register for an account for this portal you click the <strong>\"Register\" </strong>button which will bring up a dialog that looks something like this:</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" width=\"791\" height=\"486\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" /></p><p>The <strong>\"D</strong><strong>isplay Name\"</strong> here is the username you wish to sign in with, the <strong>\"E</strong><strong>mail\"</strong> address should be filled in with your company email address. The&nbsp;<strong>\"Password\" </strong>and the <strong>\"Confirm Password\" </strong>fields need to be filled in with the password you wish to use when signing into the portal. You&nbsp;<strong>must </strong>read and agree to the terms and conditions and the data protection policy to create an account with our portals. To view these documents, click the links and you will be redirected to the page where you can read them.</p>"
    }
  ],
  "PageInfo": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Description": "This page explains how to complete registration for a cCoder portal.",
      "Keywords": "Registration",
      "Title": "Registration"
    }
  ]
}
"""
            },
            new PackageItem
            {
                Type = "Core/Page",
                Data = """
{
  "Path": "Documentation/SSODocumentation/SSOAPI",
  "Name": "SSO API",
  "ShowOnMenus": true,
  "Order": 0,
  "LastUpdated": "2024-08-22T12:04:13.1674907+01:00",
  "Layout": "Documentation",
  "Contents": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Name": "body",
      "Html": "<h2>Our SSO API</h2><p>You can use our Single Sign On (SSO) API to perform different tasks, for example you can use it to register for an account, or use it to sign into an existing account in our system.<br /></p><p>When you register for an account in our portal, it does two things:</p><ul><li>Sets up an account in our SSO database,</li><li>Adds you as a user to the portal you're registering to (this essentially gives you very minimal access to the portal, further access has to be applied for).</li></ul><p>To understand more about our SSO API, you can view more details about the possible requests you can make in our <a href=\"[app[root]]Documentation/SSODocumentation/SSOAPI/SSOMetadata\">SSO Metadata grid</a>.</p><h2>Registering using our API</h2><p>The first thing you have to do is build out your registration request, this will look something like this:</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--bs-font-monospace);font-size:0.875em;color:var(--kendo-color-on-app-surface, #212529);font-weight:var(--bs-body-font-weight);text-align:var(--bs-body-text-align);\">HTTP POST </span><a href=\"https://%3Cappurl%3E/Api/Account/Login\">https://&lt;AppURL&gt;/Api/Account/Login</a></p><pre style=\"background-color:#ffffff;font-family:var(--bs-font-monospace);font-size:12px;\">        {\n            DisplayName: \"Joe Bloggs\",\n            Email:\"joe.bloggs@corporatelinx.com\",\n            Password:\"superSecretPassword123!!\",\n            Culture: \"en-GB\",\n            PhoneNumber: \"01234 567 890\",\n            AppId: 0\n        }</pre><p>AppId is an optional field (it doesn't matter if you don't have one, providing one will automatically register the account with in the app with that particular Id).</p><p>The rest of this information is standard information that you would expect to have to provide on any account creation.</p><h2>Logging in using our API</h2><p>You can now use the details you just set up to authenticate and get a token. This request will look something like this:</p><p><span style=\"font-family:var(--bs-font-monospace);font-size:0.875em;color:var(--kendo-color-on-app-surface, #212529);font-weight:var(--bs-body-font-weight);text-align:var(--bs-body-text-align);\">HTTP POST&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://%3Cappurl%3E/Api/Account/Register\">https://&lt;AppURL&gt;/Api/Account/Login</a><span style=\"font-family:var(--bs-font-monospace);font-size:0.875em;color:var(--kendo-color-on-app-surface, #212529);font-weight:var(--bs-body-font-weight);text-align:var(--bs-body-text-align);\"></span></p><pre style=\"background-color:#ffffff;font-family:var(--bs-font-monospace);font-size:12px;\">        {\n            User: &ldquo;joe.bloggs@corporatelinx.com&rdquo;,\n            Pass: &ldquo;superSecretPassword123!!\"\n        }</pre><p>When this request is made, the server responds with a token which can be used in all subsequent calls you make to the API.</p>"
    }
  ],
  "PageInfo": [
    {
      "CultureId": "",
      "Description": "SSO API",
      "Keywords": "SSO API",
      "Title": "SSO API"
    }
  ]
}
"""
            }
        ]
    };
